    "fullSummary": "This meditation session guides us through an experience of deep connection with our breath. By stabilizing our gaze and becoming aware of the eye as an expansion of the brain, we learn to observe the present moment, particularly the end of exhalation. Through a loving-kindness exercise, we are encouraged to send love and tenderness to a person who comes to mind. This process not only promotes our own well-being but also enriches our relationships with others.",
    "transcriptMarkdown": "# Meditation\n\nConnect with your **breathing**.\n\nStabilise your eyes. The **eye** is an **expansion of the brain** and the **third ventricle**. Breathe.\n\nObserve the end of the **exhalation**.\n\nIn this moment, say goodbye to a **bubble** you have filled.\n\nTry to finish thinking about something. Think of someone who comes to mind, to whom you wish to send **love** or **goodness**.\n\nImagine that, through this thought, you can transmit **well-being**, **tenderness**, **love**, and **joy** to them.\n\nDo this."
